result.execSummary:
William Francis Coughlin was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means William Francis Coughlin was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
1:14 PM Call to Order by Court.  Appearances stated: Defendant William Francis Coughlin in court, in custody.  Attorney Luke Steiner appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. 

Court provides defendant with a copy of the criminal complaint, State of Minnesota, Winona county warrant and a waiver of extradition form. 

Court reviews waiver of extradition form with defendant. Defendant states understanding. 
Defendant agrees to waiver of extradition.

Defendant signs waiver of extradition. 
Court finds defendants waiver of extradition has been made freely, knowingly and voluntarily. 

Court signs waiver and provides a copy to the defendant. Sheriffs department will contact Winona county to make arrangements. 
Defendant is heard. 
End 1:31 PM
Extradition hearing on April 6, 2022 at 01:15 pm.
